      ],
      "source": "https://visitmadisonfl.com/about/"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The city was founded on land secured from Madison C., establishing its roots in early 19th‑century Florida.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        2
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://cityofmadisonfl.com/about-madison/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "A small park near the former Amtrak station preserves memories of the “cotton years,” a nod to the town’s agricultural past.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://cityofmadisonfl.com/about-madison/"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Madison once hosted an Amtrak stop on the Sunset Limited line, linking the town to coast‑to‑coast travel.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        10
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Madison%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Freight trains now run through Madison on the Florida Gulf & Atlantic Railroad, which took over the former CSX main line in 2019.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
